## Why This Is Asked

Real deployments feature streaming, nonstationary signals with packet losses; this probes online, distributed ICA under resource constraints.

## Key Concepts

- Online incremental ICA with whitening
- Masked updates for missing channels
- Distributed consensus across nodes
- Drift tracking with forgetting factor
- Evaluation with SDR/SIR and latency constraints

## Code Example

```javascript
// Pseudocode: incremental whitening and demixing
let W = I(n); // demixing
while (newBatch) {
  let X = getBatch();
  let Xc = whitenOnline(X);
  W += eta * (I - W * Xc * Xc^T);
  // apply masking for missing channels
}
```

## Follow-up Questions

- How would you validate component stability under network partitions?
- How would you extend to nonlinearity or non-Gaussian sources?

## Why This Is Asked
Tests real-time adaptive blind source separation capabilities in dynamic industrial environments, requiring integration of sensor fusion for geometric awareness and computational efficiency.

## Key Concepts
- Online convolutive ICA with time-varying mixing matrices
- STFT framing and per-bin vs joint diagonalization trade-offs
- IMU/pose priors for permutation and scale stabilization
- Forgetting factors in whitening and drift tracking mechanisms
- Real-time computational constraints and parallel processing

## Code Example
```javascript
// Online update skeleton with sensor fusion integration
function updateMixingMatrix(M_t, observations, imuData, forgettingFactor) {
  // Geometric regularization using IMU priors
  const geometricConstraint = computePoseRegularization(imuData);
  // Kalman filter update with adaptive forgetting
  const M_next = kalmanUpdate(M_t, observations, forgettingFactor, geometricConstraint);
  return M_next;
}
```

## Why This Is Asked
Tests ability to design a robust, real-time ICA pipeline under practical constraints.

## Key Concepts
- Online adaptive demixing
- Frame-based whitening (ZCA)
- Binwise vs joint diagonalization
- Dropout handling and missing-data resilience
- Real-time latency constraints and evaluation

## Code Example
```javascript
// Pseudo: online update of W
function updateW(W, X, forgetting) {
  const Y = W.matMul(X);
  const grad = computeGrad(Y, X);
  return W.sub(grad.mul(forgetting));
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you validate robustness to sudden burst noise?
- What metrics beyond SDR/SIR would you report for production?

## Why This Is Asked

Car environments introduce dynamic geometry, intermittent sensor faults, and real-time constraints. This question probes the ability to design an online ICA solution that adapts to changing mixing, handles missing data gracefully, and maintains consistent source order over time.

## Key Concepts

- Online sliding-window ICA with adaptive whitening
- Kalman-style demixer updates on whitened data
- Missing-channel handling via subspace completion without reinitialization
- Permutation stability using short temporal memory and cross-frame non-Gaussianity cues
- Real-time latency targets and robust evaluation (ground-truth SDR/SIR, perceptual checks)

## Code Example

```javascript
// Pseudocode: online update for W on whitened data Xw
function onlineUpdate(W, Xw, lr) {
  const Y = W.dot(Xw);
  const e = gradientNonGaussianity(Y);
  return W.add(e.mul(lr).dot(Xw.transpose()));
}
```

## Follow-up Questions

- How would you diagnose instability when sources cross or when dropouts occur?
- How would you scale to larger arrays with nonuniform sampling or asynchronous microphones?

## Why This Is Asked
Tests multimodal integration and practical online ICA under latency constraints.

## Key Concepts
- Multimodal cues as soft references in ICA
- Online 2×2 demixing with permutation alignment
- Lip-region signal as auxiliary bias, frame-to-frame stability

## Code Example
```javascript
// Conceptual online ICA with lip-bias (not ready-to-run)
let W = [[1,0,0,0],[0,0,1,0]]; // 2x4
for (let frame of frames) {
  let X = frame; // 4x1
  let Xc = whiten(X);
  let S = tanh(mul(W, Xc)); // 2x1
  let lip = lipSignal(frame);
  W = add(W, lr * (eye(2) - S * S^T) * Xc^T);
  W = add(W, bias * lip);
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How handle audio-video misalignment?
- How would you validate latency end-to-end?

## Why This Is Asked

Assess practical blind source separation pipeline design under real-time, network-induced constraints for collaboration tools deployed at scale.

## Key Concepts

- Streaming BSS with time-varying mixing matrices
- Synchronization strategies for asynchronous inputs and packet loss
- Joint diagonalization versus per-bin ICA trade-offs
- Latency budgeting and robustness to network jitter
- Evaluation methodology using SDR/SIR metrics plus perceptual validation

## Code Example

```javascript
// Pseudocode: online BSS for 2 sources, 4 mics
function onlineBSS(micFrames) {
  // Synchronize misaligned frames
  const syncedFrames = synchronizeStreams(micFrames);

  // STFT processing
  const stftFrames = syncedFrames.map(frame => stft(frame));

  // Estimate time-varying mixing matrix
  const mixingMatrix = estimateMixingMatrix(stftFrames);

  // Apply spatially varying whitening
  const whitened = spatialWhitening(stftFrames, mixingMatrix);

  // Joint diagonalization for source separation
  const separatedSources = jointDiagonalization(whitened);

  return separatedSources;
}
```

## Why This Is Asked
Tests ability to design a practical real-time BSS for a CPU-constrained setup with non-stationary noise.

## Key Concepts
- Real-time ICA, frame-based processing, whitening, online demixing, permutation alignment, non-stationary noise tracking
- Trade-offs: time vs frequency domain, learning-rate stability, latency, evaluation

## Code Example
```javascript
function onlineDemix(X, W, lr){
  // X: frame batch, W: demixing, lr: learning rate
  const Y = W.map((w,i)=> dot(w, X[i]));
  // simple gradient update placeholder
  const dW = Y.map((y, idx)=> (X[idx] * (sign(y))));
```

## Why This Is Asked

Tests practical design of online ICA under non-stationarity and real-time constraints, a common challenge in wearables and streaming data.

## Key Concepts

- Online ICA with streaming whitening
- Adaptive contrast/Nonlinearity choices
- Drift tracking for sign and permutation

## Code Example

```javascript
// Pseudo online ICA update (simplified)
function updateUnmixing(W, X_batch) {
  const Y = W.map(row => dot(row, X_batch));
  // compute a simple contrast derivative estimate
  const dW = computeGradient(Y, X_batch);
  // stochastic update
  return W.map((w, i) => normalizeVector(subtract(w, scale(dW[i], 0.01))));
}
```

